cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.CE 

This paper deals with the problem of channel state information at the transmitter (CSIT) in a multiple-input single-output (MISO) broadcast channel (BC). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also presents a novel scheme for utilizing hybrid channel knowledge, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of multiple antennas, which could be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper presents results on the degrees of freedom, which could be relevant to cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
